Name{number}
	advblue - AdvanceMAME Bluetooth Daemon

Synopsis
	:advblue [-f]

Description
	The `advblue' utility is a daemon that is able to
	pair and connect Bluetooth joysticks automatically.

	It uses the /usr/bin/bluetoothctl tool to communicate
	with the devices.

	To start it, simply run it without any arguments.

Options
	The following command-line option is supported:

	-f
		Run in foreground mode. Interaction with the
		bluetoothctl program is printed on the terminal.

